    <licenseUrl>https://github.com/SosomLab/nexa-dir2/blob/main/LICENSE.md</licenseUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>true</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <projectSourceUrl>https://github.com/SosomLab/nexa-dir2</projectSourceUrl>
    <docsUrl>https://github.com/SosomLab/nexa-dir2/tree/main/docs</docsUrl>
    <bugTrackerUrl>https://github.com/SosomLab/nexa-dir2/issues</bugTrackerUrl>
    <tags>nexa-dir file-manager explorer windows rust portable admin</tags>
    <summary>Lightweight, keyboard-first file explorer for Windows — portable single exe.</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[
**Nexa Dir** is a lightweight file explorer for Windows, built as a single native
executable in pure Rust on the Win32 API — no managed runtime, no UI framework,
no external DLLs beyond the OS inbox set.

This is the **portable** edition: one executable, no installer, no Start Menu
entry. For the installed edition, use the `nexa-dir` package instead.

### Highlights

* **Single portable exe** — under 10 MB, idle memory footprint under 30 MB.
* **Dense, dark, keyboard-first UI** — designed for fast navigation over the mouse.
* **Virtualized tree/list** — smooth over 100k+ entries.
* **Bulk rename** with reusable presets, built-in preview, dual-language UI (English/Korean).

### Notes

* The executable is placed in the package's `tools` folder and exposed on PATH
  through a Chocolatey shim, so you can launch it by running `NexaDir`.
* The portable build keeps its settings and session in a `data\` folder next to
  the executable. Because that folder lives inside the package directory,
  **`choco uninstall` removes your settings along with the package.** Use the
  `nexa-dir` package if you want settings preserved across uninstalls.

### License

Nexa Dir is released under the **PolyForm Noncommercial License 1.0.0** — free for
personal and other noncommercial use. **Commercial use requires a separate paid
license** — see https://sosomlab.com/apps/nexa-dir/ for licensing.

Product home: https://sosomlab.com/apps/nexa-dir/
]]></description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/SosomLab/nexa-dir2/releases</releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <file src="tools\**" target="tools" />
  </files>
</package>
